{"kanda":6,"sarga":21,"description":"","verses":[{"v":1,"dev":"ततस्सागरवेलायांदर्भानास्तीर्यराघवः ।अञ्जलिंप्राङ्मुखःकृत्वाप्रतिशिश्येमहोदधेः बाहुंभुजगभोगाभमुपधायारिसूदनः ।","trans":"Then Raghava the destroyer of foes, offered his obeisance turning his face towards east, spread the kusa grass mat on the seashore and lay down resting his head upon his shoulders like a coiled serpent.","words":[{"d":"ततः","m":"then"},{"d":"अरिसूदनः","m":"one who is a destroyer of his foes"},{"d":"राघवः","m":"Raghava"},{"d":"सागरवेलायाम्","m":"on the sea shore"},{"d":"दर्भान्","m":"on kusa grass"},{"d":"आस्तीर्य","m":"spread"},{"d":"महोदधेः","m":"great ocean"},{"d":"अञ्जलिम्","m":"obeisance"},{"d":"कृत्वा","m":"offering"},{"d":"प्राङ्मुखः","m":"face turned towards east"},{"d":"भुजगभोगाम्","m":"like serpent coiled and resting"},{"d":"बाहुम्","m":"shoulders"},{"d":"उपधाय","m":"resting upon"},{"d":"प्रतिशिश्ये","m":"lay down."}]},{"v":2,"dev":"वरकाञ्चनकेयूरमुक्ताप्रवरभूषणैः भुजैःपरमनारीणामभिमृष्टमनेकदा","trans":"The shoulders that have been adorned with the best of gold, pearl and coral ornaments, were besmeared many times by supreme women.","words":[{"d":"वरकाञ्चनकेयूरमुक्ताप्रवरभूषणैः","m":"armlet adorned with best of gold, pearls and coral ornaments"},{"d":"परमनारीणाम्","m":"by supreme women"},{"d":"भुजैः","m":"shoulders"},{"d":"अनेकाथा","m":"many times"},{"d":"अभिमृष्टम्","m":"besmeared."}]},{"v":3,"dev":"वरकाञ्चनकेयूरमुक्ताप्रवरभूषणैः भुजैःपरमनारीणामभिमृष्टमनेकदा","trans":"The shoulders that have been adorned with the best of gold, pearl and coral ornaments, were besmeared many times by supreme women.","words":[{"d":"वरकाञ्चनकेयूरमुक्ताप्रवरभूषणैः","m":"armlet adorned with best of gold, pearls and coral ornaments"},{"d":"परमनारीणाम्","m":"by supreme women"},{"d":"भुजैः","m":"shoulders"},{"d":"अनेकाथा","m":"many times"},{"d":"अभिमृष्टम्","m":"besmeared."}]},{"v":4,"dev":"चन्दनागुरुभिश्चैवपुरस्तादधिवासितम् ।बालसूर्यप्रकाशैश्चन्दनैरुपशोभितम्","trans":"The very charming shoulders, smeared